# scheduler-api environment (names only — fill with your own values)
#
# Copy to `.env` (or export in your shell) for local dev. Every value is
# project-specific and comes from your own infrastructure; nothing is baked in.
# The server reads these via os.Getenv at startup — see cmd/scheduler-api/main.go
# and internal/webhooks/whatsapp/.

# --- HTTP server ---------------------------------------------------------
# Port the API listens on. Optional; defaults to 8080 when unset.
PORT=8080

# --- Firebase / tenant auth ----------------------------------------------
# The Firebase/GCP project whose Firebase ID tokens are accepted. The actor's
# identity and role are derived ONLY from the verified token. Either var works;
# FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID takes precedence, then GCLOUD_PROJECT.
FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-firebase-project-id
GCLOUD_PROJECT=your-gcloud-project-id

# Dev-local ONLY: point at the Firebase Auth emulator to accept its unsigned
# tokens. Leave UNSET in any real/staging/production environment.
# FIREBASE_AUTH_EMULATOR_HOST=localhost:9099

# --- WhatsApp Business webhook (Meta Graph API) --------------------------
# Token you configure in the Meta webhook setup; the GET verification handshake
# must echo it back. Treat as a shared secret.
WHATSAPP_VERIFY_TOKEN=your_webhook_verify_token

# Meta App Secret used to validate the X-Hub-Signature-256 HMAC on inbound
# webhook payloads. Treat as a secret.
WHATSAPP_APP_SECRET=your_meta_app_secret

# Graph API access token used to download inbound media. Treat as a secret.
WHATSAPP_TOKEN=your_graph_api_token

# Storage bucket that downloaded media is written to.
WHATSAPP_MEDIA_BUCKET=your-media-bucket

# Graph API version segment for media URLs. Optional; defaults to v21.0.
# WHATSAPP_GRAPH_VERSION=v21.0

# Internal-only: when truthy ("1"/"true"/"yes"/"on") inbound webhook events are
# also forwarded to an internal Slack channel for human review. Defaults OFF
# (fail-closed) — leave unset/empty unless you wire your own SlackNotifier.
# WHATSAPP_NOTIFY_SLACK=
